-- Zambian Police Charge Chinese Mine Managers After Workers Shot, Wounded
-- B y   O b e r t   S i m w a n z a
-- 2010-10-18T14:31:44Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-18/zambian-police-charge-chinese-mine-managers-after-workers-shot-wounded.html
Zambian police arrested two Chinese
managers at Collum Mine for the shooting and wounding of 11
miners during a protest over pay and working conditions, Oliver
Pelete, district commissioner for Sinazongwe, said by phone.   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
